  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once your Q (Lay Waste) is rank 2-3 you out-range Sivir's Boomerang Blade and can chip her every time she steps up to farm; hold E (Defile) until she Spell Shields, then walk in and drop it after her shield pops."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Requiem) turns any low-HP recall or roam into a free kill, and it punishes Sivir hard because her only defensive tool is Spell Shield on a long cooldown that does nothing against an already-cast global; ping and fire when she backs low."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Liandry's or Blackfire Torch online your Q burst plus E DoT out-trades Sivir's raw AA damage; she has to On The Hunt away rather than duel you, so shove and roam off the pressure."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 Sivir's ult peels for her team, but your death passive and E melt her clumped comp while she can't Spell Shield the whole Requiem; play behind your frontline and E onto the grouped fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Q poke landing on Sivir as she last-hits","E turned on after her Spell Shield is spent","grouped fights where E and R hit her whole team"],"foe":["Spell Shielding your Q or E to nullify the trade","using her Q+W wave-clear to shove you under tower","On The Hunt engages that close the range gap"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Sivir is ahead: her Boomerang Blade plus Ricochet push the wave into you and let her poke on the shove while you have only a rank-1 Q, and her Spell Shield eats your first Lay Waste for free. Respect the early shove, farm safely, and don't waste Q into her shield window.","mid":"By level 3-6 the lane flips as your Q ranks up and out-ranges her; bait the Spell Shield with a fake Q or your E step, then land real damage. Level 6 Requiem makes every low back a death sentence she can't shield against.","late":"With a completed first item your Q+E burst beats her sustained AAs and she can only kite with On The Hunt; in teamfights space behind minions, E the clumped enemies, and hold Requiem for the execute her shield can't stop.","whys":["Sivir's rank-1 Boomerang and Ricochet shove the wave and let her poke you first at level 1.","At level 2 her Spell Shield still trivializes your single Q and she controls the wave.","Through level 3 her push tempo and shield keep her the safer, more threatening laner.","By levels 4-5 your ranked-up Q out-ranges Boomerang and you win the poke war.","Your level 6 Requiem executes low Sivir backs that her Spell Shield cannot prevent.","A completed first item makes your Q+E burst out-trade her raw auto damage.","In late teamfights your death passive and E melt her grouped comp faster than she can peel."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is a scaling stack-machine who is weak before his Q (Super Scorcher Breath) stacks up; abuse that with rank-2/3 Lay Waste, chunking him every time he walks up to farm and denying the CS he needs for stacks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Requiem punishes his passive greed: when he stays low to keep farming stacks, a global execute ends him, and he has no mobility outside a short W (Achewind Blast) hop to dodge it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item's burst you win every short trade before his stacks mature; keep the wave in the middle so his E (Mazel Tov) escape can't reach tower and he must risk your Q+E to CS."},{"when":"Late","text":"Smolder scales hard but if you starved his stacks he never reaches his Dragon Q threshold; in fights your E melts him through his flame and your death passive keeps damaging even if he bursts you."}],"wants":{"you":["Q harass every time Smolder steps up for stacks","denying his early CS so his Q never matures","level 6 Requiem executing his greedy low-HP farming"],"foe":["free-farming stacks safely under tower","reaching the 225-stack Dragon Q spike","using E to escape your all-in and reset"]},"early":"You own levels 1-2: Smolder is one of the weakest early ADCs before his Q stacks, and your Lay Waste pokes him off the wave with no risk. Land Q on him as he last-hits and set up a support all-in while he has no damage or escape.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours as your Q out-ranges his early rank-1 Q and your E punishes any step-up. At 6 your Requiem executes him for farming greedily, so ping and fire whenever he lingers low for CS.","late":"If you denied stacks he never comes fully online; your first-item burst and E DoT beat him in short trades. In teamfights space behind minions and E onto him, letting your death passive finish the job even through his flame breath.","whys":["Smolder is at his weakest pre-stacks and your rank-1 Q pokes him for free at level 1.","At level 2 he still has no damage or escape while your Q keeps chipping him.","Level 3 your ranked Q and E out-trade his unstacked kit.","Levels 4-5 you deny the CS he needs and dominate the poke war.","Your level 6 Requiem executes his greedy low-HP farming that his kit can't prevent.","A first item makes your burst beat him before his stacks ever mature.","Late, a starved Smolder folds to your E and death passive in grouped fights."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain support/bot bullies you early: his W (Vision of Empire) zones your farm and his E (Nevermove) root plus Q (Death's Hand) burst threaten a lethal all-in your fragile body can't survive; hug the wall and don't get hooked by E."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Swain's level 6 Demonic Ascension gives him massive sustain and lifedrain in an all-in, out-healing your Q poke; avoid extended fights and just farm from max Lay Waste range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane finally turns: with your first item Liandry's/Torch, your Q+E DoT out-damages his healing and your Requiem starts executing him after he drops out of ult; poke him below the threshold and finish globally."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 you stay far behind Swain's frontline; your E and death passive shred his grouped, tanky-drain comp while he peels, and Requiem picks off carries his root can't protect."}],"wants":{"you":["max-range Q farming outside his E root","first-item DoT that beats his ult healing","Requiem executing Swain after Demonic Ascension ends"],"foe":["landing E (Nevermove) root into Q+W all-in","Demonic Ascension sustain in extended trades","using W zone to deny your CS and push you in"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Swain: his E root sets up a Q burst combo that can delete you, and his W zones the wave so you farm on the back foot. Never step where his E can land, give up CS if you must, and keep your Flash for the root all-in.","mid":"Levels 4-6 Swain stays ahead as Demonic Ascension gives him drain-tank sustain that out-heals your poke, so don't duel him. Farm from max Lay Waste range and wait for your item spike rather than trading into his ult.","late":"Once your first item is online the matchup flips to you: your Q+E DoT beats his healing and Requiem executes him after his ult drops. In fights hold the backline, E his grouped comp, and let your death passive keep ticking through his engage.","whys":["Swain's early E root plus Q burst threatens a lethal all-in your fragile ADC body can't survive.","At level 2 his W zone and burst keep you pinned and farming on the back foot.","Level 3 his root-into-combo all-in still dominates the short lane.","Levels 4-5 his kit pressure keeps you zoned before your items arrive.","Level 6 Demonic Ascension's sustain out-heals your poke in any extended trade.","With your first item your Q+E DoT finally out-damages his healing and Requiem executes him.","Late, your E and death passive shred his grouped drain comp from safe range."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tristana has almost no range early (her AA range grows with level), so your Lay Waste out-ranges her hard; poke her every time she walks up and punish any Rocket Jump (W) in with an instant E turn-on and support CC."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Requiem executes her when she dives with W, and it also punishes the low-HP state she puts herself in after jumping; if she W's onto you, E and let your death passive plus R clean her up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item, your Q burst plus E DoT beat her before her AA range and Explosive Charge (E) stacks come online; keep the wave central so her W engage is a coin-flip into your all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tristana becomes a hyper-late threat but you group and let your E and death passive punish her all-in; when she W-Q jumps the backline she lands low and your Requiem or death-ticking E finishes her."}],"wants":{"you":["Q poke abusing her short early AA range","punishing her Rocket Jump with E + support CC","Requiem executing her post-jump low-HP state"],"foe":["stacking Explosive Charge for burst reset kills","using W to gap-close and dodge your Q","scaling to her long-range late-game auto pattern"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: Tristana's early auto range is among the shortest, so your Lay Waste chips her freely while she can barely reach the wave. Poke her off CS and set up a level-2 all-in if your support has CC, since she has no escape charge yet.","mid":"Levels 3-6 you keep the poke lead; if she Rocket Jumps in, instantly E and burst her, and at 6 your Requiem executes her low post-jump. Don't let her stack Explosive Charge on you for free, and keep spacing behind your minions.","late":"Tristana out-scales most ADCs, but you play for teamfights where your E and death passive punish her dive; when she W-Q's your backline she lands low, and Requiem or your ticking E finishes her before her reset lands.","whys":["Tristana's tiny early auto range lets your rank-1 Q poke her for free at level 1.","At level 2 she still can't reach you while your Q keeps chipping her off CS.","Level 3 your ranged poke and E punish any Rocket Jump engage.","Levels 4-5 you hold the poke lead and she can't stack E on you safely.","Your level 6 Requiem executes her low-HP state after she jumps in.","A first item makes your Q+E burst beat her before her scaling comes online.","Late, your E and death passive punish her all-in dives in grouped fights."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch is a weak early laner who relies on Ambush (Q) stealth to reposition; your Lay Waste out-ranges his short AAs and your E reveals and punishes him if he tries to stealth up to you, so poke him off every CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Requiem executes him when he burns HP stacking Deadly Venom, and your E instantly cancels his Ambush stealth if he tries to reposition for a Rat-Ta-Tat-Tat (R) angle; hold R for his low backs."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your Q+E burst out-trades his early auto poke before his Contaminate (E) six-stack payoff comes online; keep the wave central so his stealth flanks have nowhere safe to land."},{"when":"Late","text":"Twitch is a lethal teamfighter with Spray and Pray, but you sit behind your frontline; if he stealths in your E reveals him instantly and your death passive plus Requiem punish the squishy body he has to expose."}],"wants":{"you":["Q poke abusing his weak short-range early","E revealing and cancelling his Ambush stealth","Requiem punishing his low-HP flanks and backs"],"foe":["stacking Deadly Venom then Contaminate for burst","using Ambush stealth to reposition and flank","reaching Spray and Pray teamfight range late"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: Twitch is one of the weakest early ADCs with short autos and no waveclear, so your Lay Waste pokes him freely. Set up an all-in if he steps up, and remember your E will reveal him the moment he tries to Ambush toward you.","mid":"Levels 3-6 you keep control; poke him off CS with Q, turn on E to cancel any stealth approach, and at 6 hold Requiem to execute his low HP after he over-extends. Don't let him freely stack Deadly Venom on you.","late":"Twitch is a deadly late teamfighter, but you play behind your frontline and let your E strip his stealth the instant he flanks; your death passive keeps damaging if he bursts you, and Requiem finishes the squishy body he must expose to fire Spray and Pray.","whys":["Twitch's weak short-range early lets your rank-1 Q poke him freely at level 1.","At level 2 he still has no waveclear or range while your Q chips him off CS.","Level 3 your ranged poke and stealth-revealing E out-control him.","Levels 4-5 you deny his stacks and hold the poke lead.","Your level 6 Requiem executes his low-HP over-extensions.","A first item makes your Q+E burst beat him before his Contaminate payoff.","Late, your E strips his stealth flanks and your death passive punishes his exposed body."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus out-ranges and out-pokes you early: his fully-charged Piercing Arrow (Q) hits harder and farther than your Lay Waste, and his W (Blighted Quiver) stacks make his poke sting; play behind minions so his Q can't punch through and don't get caught by a charged shot."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Varus's Chain of Corruption (R) is a long-range root that sets up a support all-in you can't escape; respect his level 6 all-in threat, keep Flash up, and don't stand in E (Hail of Arrows) zones during trades."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane turns to you here: with your first item your Q+E DoT out-damages his poke, and once you can survive his combo your Requiem executes him from range after he blows Q; poke him below the threshold and finish."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 Varus threatens from range but you sit behind your frontline; your E and death passive shred his team in grouped fights and Requiem snipes him or a low carry his single R can't cover."}],"wants":{"you":["first-item DoT that out-damages his poke","surviving his Q+R combo to reach your spike","Requiem executing him after he burns Piercing Arrow"],"foe":["landing charged Piercing Arrow through your minions","Blighted Quiver stacks amplifying his early poke","Chain of Corruption root setting up the all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Varus: his charged Q out-ranges your Lay Waste and his W-stack poke chips you down before you can answer. Farm behind your minions so his Piercing Arrow can't pierce to you, dodge his E zones, and don't trade into a full W-stack detonation.","mid":"Through level 6 Varus stays ahead thanks to his Chain of Corruption root enabling a lethal support all-in on your fragile body. Keep Flash up, don't over-extend past your wave, and just farm safely until your first item arrives.","late":"Once your first item is online the matchup flips: your Q+E DoT out-damages his poke and Requiem executes him after he commits Q. In teamfights hold the backline, E his grouped comp, and let your death passive keep ticking while Requiem snipes a low carry.","whys":["Varus's charged Piercing Arrow out-ranges and out-pokes your rank-1 Q at level 1.","At level 2 his Blighted Quiver stacks amplify his poke and keep you on the back foot.","Level 3 his range and stack poke keep the lane in his favour.","Levels 4-5 his Q poke and E zoning still control the wave before your items land.","Varus's level 6 Chain of Corruption root sets up an all-in your fragile body can't escape.","With your first item your Q+E DoT out-damages his poke and Requiem executes him.","Late, your E and death passive shred his grouped comp from safe backline range."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q Lay Waste maxed you out-poke Vayne at range every wave: she has to walk into your minions to auto or Tumble a Silver Bolt proc, and each step forward eats a splash-empowered Lay Waste. Land two clean center-hits and she can't contest last hits without dropping below your all-in threshold."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Requiem is a lane-wide execute that ignores Vayne's Q reposition entirely; if she recalls low or your support lands CC, you can R for a free kill from fog. Her level 6 Final Hour gives stealth on Tumble but does nothing against a global that only needs her health bar low."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item spike (Liandry's/Blackfire or Luden's line) turns every Q into a chunk, while Vayne's Botrk spike is single-target and needs her on top of you. Hold Wall of Pain to knife her the instant she Tumbles in, then E Defile as she's slowed and she melts before three-stacking bolts."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights Vayne wants to isolate a carry with Condemn, but you fight from the second row spamming Q and threatening a passive-Requiem chain. Your Death Defiance means even a clean Condemn-stun into her burst still gives you 7 seconds of zombie casts to finish the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke her down with center-hit Lay Waste before she can stack Silver Bolts","Track her low-health moments across the map to steal kills with Requiem","Use Wall of Pain to zone her Tumble angle and peel her all-in"],"foe":["Close the gap and three-stack Silver Bolts on you with Tumble resets","Use Final Hour stealth to dodge your Q and reset her attack timings","Isolate you against a wall for a Condemn stun into full burst"]},"early":"Lay Waste out-ranges every tool Vayne has at levels 1-2; sit behind your caster minions and punish her the moment she walks up to farm, since she has no wave clear and no poke to answer your Q. Keep your mana for last-hits and one or two center-hits per wave rather than shoving.","mid":"From 3 onward your Q max and E Defile give you both a poke lead and a short-range shred if she dives; she can't trade auto-for-Q profitably until Botrk. At 6 Requiem flips any low-health recall into a kill, so watch her HP bar even when she leaves lane.","late":"With one item online your Q burst plus Death Defiance passive make you nearly impossible to kill in a straight all-in, and in 5v5 you play behind frontline slinging Lay Waste while Vayne struggles to reach you. Threaten Requiem picks and let your zombie form clean up anyone who dove your backline.","whys":["Karthus Q out-ranges Vayne's short auto range so you poke freely at level 1.","At level 2 your Q rank plus early E threat still beats Vayne's no-poke laning.","Level 3 Q max lets you chunk her every time she steps up to farm.","Levels 4-5 you keep the poke lead before Vayne's Botrk spike arrives.","Level 6 Requiem executes her from anywhere, adding kill pressure she can't match.","First-item Q burst out-damages her single-target Botrk all-in.","With 2+ items your poke and Death Defiance passive dominate the 2v2 and teamfight."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Both of you are skillshot pokers, but your Q Lay Waste has a shorter cast time and lower mana cost than Veigar's Baleful Strike, so you win the raw poke war and deny his passive AP stacks by not dying to his farm-Q. Sidestep his Baleful and punish the cooldown with a center-hit; his wave clear also pushes into you, letting you freeze and starve his stacking."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Requiem is instant, targeted and unavoidable, whereas Veigar's R Primordial Burst needs you low and him in range; if you keep your HP healthy his ult can't execute you but yours threatens him constantly. Respect his E Event Horizon cage into R combo, but a whiffed cage leaves him with no burst for a long window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item AP spike makes every Lay Waste a real chunk while your E Defile shreds anyone who walks into his cage range; Veigar's spike is the same item timing, so the lead comes down to who lands more skillshots and dodges the cage. Buy an early MR component or Merc treads to blunt his combo."},{"when":"Late","text":"Veigar is the one caster who can genuinely one-shot you if he lands cage-R, so in teamfights you must space outside Event Horizon and Wall of Pain his approach angle. Your Death Defiance passive is the trump card: even eating his full combo, you get 7 seconds of unstoppable Requiem-and-Q casts to win the fight from the grave."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the poke war with faster, cheaper Lay Waste and deny his stacks","Stay above his R execute threshold so Primordial Burst can't kill you","Space outside Event Horizon so he can never land cage into R"],"foe":["Stack AP off Baleful Strike last-hits and poke you with it","Land Event Horizon cage into Primordial Burst for a one-shot","Zone you off waves and objectives with his long-range stun"]},"early":"This is a mirror-style caster lane and your Lay Waste simply out-trades Baleful Strike on cast speed and mana, so poke him whenever he steps up and refuse to feed his passive by dodging his farm-Q. Freeze if you can to choke his infinite AP stacking, and never stand in a spot where his support can root you into a free Baleful.","mid":"From 3-6 keep winning the skillshot exchange and hold Wall of Pain to break his Event Horizon approach; his only kill setup is cage-into-burst, which you deny by spacing. At 6 your Requiem pressures him globally while his R can't touch you unless you let your HP drop into execute range.","late":"With items online you both hit hard, but you play from max range slinging Q and E-shredding anyone near his cage, and your Death Defiance means a landed combo on you still ends with a full zombie-cast rotation. Build an early MR piece, respect the one-shot angle, and out-DPS him from safety in every 5v5.","whys":["Your Lay Waste out-casts Baleful Strike at level 1 for a poke edge.","At level 2 faster, cheaper Q keeps you ahead in the caster trade.","Level 3 Q max lets you deny his stacks and win exchanges outright.","Levels 4-5 you keep the poke lead as long as you dodge his cage.","Your instant Requiem threatens him while his R can't execute a healthy you.","At first item your Q burst and E shred match his spike with more safety.","With 2+ items your range and Death Defiance passive win the 2v2 and teamfight."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early, Xayah out-trades you: her Double Daggers empower autos and her feather passive lets her farm and poke without ever standing still for your Lay Waste, while her Deadly Plumage attack-speed steroid shreds you in a straight fight. Your Q is a delayed skillshot she sidesteps by weaving feathers, so keep it defensive, last-hit safely, and don't walk into her Bladecaller root-line."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is where you flip it: Requiem punishes her all-in commitment since her Featherstorm ult is only a short untargetable dodge, not immunity to a global execute. If she blows Featherstorm to survive your support's CC, she still dies to a delayed Requiem once it lands, and she has no way to reposition out of it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With one item your Q burst and E Defile turn a shove into real damage, and Xayah's own root relies on stacking feathers on the ground, which you deny by staying mobile behind your minions. Your Wall of Pain also ruins her Bladecaller recall timing and peels her Deadly Plumage dive; play for pick pressure rather than a raw DPS race."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights Xayah out-DPSes you if she free-hits, but she must commit forward to line up a Bladecaller root, which is exactly when you E Defile, Wall her, and threaten a passive-Requiem chain from the back line. Your Death Defiance means even her burst plus a feather root leaves you 7 seconds of zombie casts to answer, tilting extended fights your way."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the early feather poke and farm safely to your level 6 spike","Punish her Featherstorm commitment with a follow-up Requiem execute","Stay mobile behind minions so her Bladecaller feathers can't root you"],"foe":["Weave feathers and Double Daggers to out-trade you before 6","Steroid up with Deadly Plumage and all-in when you step up","Land a Bladecaller root to lock you for her burst and support follow-up"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Xayah: her feather mechanics let her poke and farm without exposing herself to Lay Waste, and Deadly Plumage wins any auto-trade, so play passive, take safe last-hits under tower, and never stand on stacked feathers. Keep Wall of Pain ready purely as a defensive peel and concede a little CS rather than eating a Bladecaller root into her all-in.","mid":"You stabilize once Q is maxed and level 6 lands: Requiem executes her even through Featherstorm's dodge window, so play for a support-CC into R kill rather than a straight DPS fight she still wins. Use Wall of Pain to break her dive angle and E Defile if she over-commits to root you.","late":"With items your poke and pick threat overtake her lane bully phase; you fight from max range, punish every forward Bladecaller setup with E and Wall, and your Death Defiance guarantees a full zombie rotation even if she bursts you. Prioritize picking her before fights start so her team loses its main damage.","whys":["Xayah's feather poke and Double Daggers out-trade your delayed Q at level 1.","At level 2 her Deadly Plumage steroid wins any auto exchange against you.","Level 3 she still bullies you with feather farming and Bladecaller threat.","By levels 4-5 your Q max stabilizes the lane back in your favor.","Level 6 Requiem executes her even through Featherstorm, flipping the kill pressure.","First-item Q burst plus Wall peel let you punish her all-in commitment.","With 2+ items your range, pick threat, and Death Defiance win the teamfight."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri's early Q Burst Fire is short-range and mana-hungry, so before she's online you out-poke her with Lay Waste every time she creeps up to farm; she can't wave clear efficiently and takes a chunk each step forward. Land center-hits when she uses W Ultrashock Laser and misses, and freeze to deny her the scaling she desperately needs."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Requiem punishes Zeri's low-HP dashes: her E Spark Surge lets her skirmish aggressively, but a global execute doesn't care how mobile she is once her health bar drops. If she over-extends on a hard-shove or gets caught by your support, R closes the deal from fog no matter how many walls she dashes through."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item AP spike keeps every Q relevant while Zeri's real power is still ramping toward her crit-and-attack-speed scaling; punish this window hard. Use Wall of Pain to kill her E dash momentum and E Defile if she Spark Surges onto you, since her early survivability is thin before items."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zeri scales into a monster who kites teamfights forever, so your win condition is ending before she comes fully online and threatening Requiem picks on her whenever she's low. In fights you space from the back, W-slow her mobility, and rely on Death Defiance so even her sustained DPS gives you a full zombie-cast window to answer."}],"wants":{"you":["Out-poke and freeze early to deny Zeri her critical scaling","Punish her low-HP skirmish dashes with a global Requiem","Use Wall of Pain to kill her E dash momentum in trades"],"foe":["Farm safely to items and come online as a hyperscaling kiter","Use E Spark Surge and walls to dodge your Q and skirmish","Ramp attack speed and crit to out-DPS you in the late game"]},"early":"Zeri is weak and mana-starved at levels 1-2, so abuse her with Lay Waste the moment she walks up: she has no answer to your poke range and can't clear waves to push you off. Freeze the lane to starve her scaling and land center-hits when her W laser whiffs, keeping her permanently behind the item curve she lives on.","mid":"Through 3-6 your Q max and E Defile keep her suppressed; she wants to skirmish with Spark Surge but every low-HP dash feeds your level 6 Requiem execute. Hold Wall of Pain to break her dash angle and deny the aggressive trades she needs to snowball out of a losing lane.","late":"If the game runs long Zeri becomes a top-tier kiter, so your job is to have banked a lead and to threaten Requiem picks on her the instant she dips low. Play from max range in fights, slow her with Wall, and trust Death Defiance to buy a full zombie rotation even if her sustained damage catches you.","whys":["Zeri's short, mana-hungry early Q loses the poke war to your Lay Waste.","At level 2 you keep chunking her every time she steps up to farm.","Level 3 Q max lets you suppress her and deny her scaling.","Levels 4-5 your poke and freeze keep her behind the item curve.","Level 6 Requiem executes her low-HP skirmish dashes she relies on.","First-item Q burst punishes her before her crit scaling comes online.","With 2+ items you must leverage your lead and picks before she out-scales."]},
  {"a":"karthus_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs out-ranges and out-pokes you early: his Q Bouncing Bomb travels farther than Lay Waste and his W Satchel Charge plus E minefield zone you off the wave and out of your own Q range. He shoves faster than you clear, denying your last hits under tower, so play safe, dodge Q bounces, and don't stand in his E mines when you step up to farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His lead holds through 6 because his own R Mega Inferno Bomb is a long-range execute-poke that matches your Requiem's global threat while he keeps out-ranging you in lane. Respect that his ult can chunk you from screens away, and keep your HP up so neither his R nor his Q combo brings you into kill range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Here the matchup flips toward you: your first-item AP spike makes Lay Waste hit hard enough to trade back, and your Requiem out-ranges everything for pick pressure while Ziggs remains an immobile, dash-less target. Hold Wall of Pain and E Defile to punish any all-in his support tries, since he has zero escape once you or your support close in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, you win by exploiting his immobility: Requiem executes him globally, Wall of Pain locks his only escape angle, and in teamfights you both poke from the back but you carry Death Defiance as insurance. Whereas he simply dies if flanked, your passive gives 7 seconds of zombie casts, so extended fights and pick-focused compositions favor you."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his early range advantage and scale to your first-item flip","Punish his total immobility with Requiem picks and support all-ins","Use Wall of Pain to cut off his one Satchel escape angle"],"foe":["Zone you off the wave with long-range Q bounces and E mines","Out-poke and out-shove you before your item spike lands","Chunk you from range with Mega Inferno Bomb to keep you low"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Ziggs: his Q out-ranges your Lay Waste and his W/E zone control shoves you in and denies farm, so accept a passive early game and last-hit carefully under tower. Dodge his Bouncing Bomb angles, never stand in his minefield when you walk up, and keep Wall of Pain for defense rather than aggression until you spike.","mid":"You stay behind until items, but at 6 your Requiem starts matching his ranged pressure and setting up picks on an immobile target. Keep your HP healthy against his R poke, and wait for your first item to convert the lane from a losing poke war into a threat game built on his lack of escape.","late":"With one item online the matchup flips: your Q trades hurt, Requiem executes him from anywhere, and Wall of Pain plus E Defile punish his complete immobility in any all-in. Play for picks with your support, and trust Death Defiance to give you a full zombie rotation that a dash-less Ziggs can never answer in a teamfight.","whys":["Ziggs' Q out-ranges Lay Waste, so he pokes and zones you at level 1.","At level 2 his W and E mines control the wave and deny your trades.","Level 3 he keeps out-ranging and out-shoving you off farm.","Levels 4-5 his lane lead holds as he chunks you from range.","At 6 your Requiem matches his ranged threat and flips kill pressure to you.","First-item Q burst and pick threat punish his total immobility.","With 2+ items your range, picks, and Death Defiance win the teamfight."]}
